cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AR, cs.SY, cs.NE 

The paper focuses on training deep learning models on a mobile device, specifically the NVIDIA TX2. This involves understanding the performance characterization of the training process, which is critical for designing and implementing deep learning models on mobile devices. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AR (Augmented Reality and Virtual Reality), which are all related to deep learning and mobile devices. Additionally, the paper discusses hardware utilization and power consumption, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), respectively.
